    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix abort on N_RB_DL=15 in LTE synchronization functions\n\n### Summary\nThe LTE synchronization code in lte_sync_time.c contains two functions that switch on N_RB_DL values to select the appropriate IDFT size. However, both functions are missing the case for N_RB_DL=15, which is a valid configuration according to the LTE specification and is defined in the N_RB_DL_array.\n\nWhen the system is configured with 15 resource blocks, these functions hit the default case and call abort(), causing the entire process to terminate unexpectedly.\n\nThis fix adds the missing case for N_RB_DL=15 in both the doIdft() function and the ru_sync_time_init() switch statements.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_ESTIMATION/lte_sync_time.c`: Added case 15 to both switch statements mapping to IDFT_256\n- Verified mapping consistency with lte_parms.c where N_RB_DL=15 maps to ofdm_symbol_size=256\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure an LTE system with N_RB_DL=15 (a valid configuration according to 3GPP specs)\n2. Run the LTE synchronization procedures\n3. The process will abort with \"Unsupported N_RB_DL 15\" message\n4. System will terminate unexpectedly instead of handling the valid configuration\n\nThe fix ensures that systems configured with 15 resource blocks can operate normally without unexpected termination.\n"
}